Web FormsBlazor <pre><code>&lt;asp:Button ID="btnSubmit" runat="server" Text="Submit" OnClick="btnSubmit_Click" /&gt;

&lt;asp:Label ID="lblResult" runat="server" /&gt;
</code></pre> <pre><code>protected void btnSubmit_Click(object sender, EventArgs e)
{
    // Handle submission
    lblResult.Text = "Form submitted!";
}
</code></pre> <pre><code>&lt;Button Text="Submit" OnClick="HandleSubmit" /&gt;

&lt;Label Text="@result" /&gt;

@code {
    private string result = "";

    private void HandleSubmit()
    {
        result = "Form submitted!";
    }
}
</code></pre> <p>Key Insight: No IsPostBack Needed</p> <p>In Blazor, you almost never need an equivalent to <code>IsPostBack</code>. The component instance persists — state is preserved naturally. Initialize data in <code>OnInitializedAsync</code>, respond to parameter changes in <code>OnParametersSetAsync</code>, and handle user interactions via event handlers. That's it.</p>

Web FormsBlazor (Without ScriptManager) <pre><code>&lt;asp:ScriptManager ID="ScriptManager1" runat="server" EnablePageMethods="true" /&gt;

